<div id="wrapper"><h2><a href="/output/Page2.asp"><img alt="" height="70" src="../files/images/XM_logo.gif" title="XM London Digital Communication" width="162" /></a></h2><h2><img alt="To explain what we do it's best to show you what we do" border="0" height="130" src="/files/images/maintitle_a_03.gif" width="256" /></h2><img class="hide" src="/files/images/clear.gif" width="1" height="1" alt="" /><h2><img width="276" alt="Our Clients and Work" height="80" border="0" src="/files/images/XM_L2_Clients_shdr.gif" /></h2><p>At XM London, we utilise an absolutely people-focused approach towards all our projects. We seek to influence and change user behaviour, to ultimately achieve the desired aims of our clients.</p><p>Our sites reach out to target audiences, so that they receive client's messages, register their details or make purchases. We do this by creating user journeys and experiences that are intuitive and natural, and by presenting brands and organisations in the most attractive way possible.</p><p>Usability and accessibility are central to all our online projects. We conduct extensive usability testing so that we know that target audiences can navigate our sites easily, and can access all content and functionality in a simple and logical manner. </p><p>We have over 150 case histories, so if you would like more information on our expertise in an area of particular interest to you, please drop us an <a href="/output/Page21.asp">email </a>or call us.</p><p>In our Awards section, you can find details of the many awards we have picked up over the years. </p><img class="hide" src="/files/images/clear.gif" width="1" height="1" alt="" />
